gomodel:SYNGO_538  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1b,h,i\nNEDD4 is synaptically localized.\nLiteral\n\"Specifically, the distribution of HA-Nedd4-1 changed from a diffuse pattern throughout dendrites and soma into a punctate pattern with tightly accumulated signal in dendritic spines (p < 0.001; Fig. 1A,C). Moreover, we found extensive colocalization of HA-Nedd4-1 with the postsynaptic density protein PSD-95 and juxtaposition to the presynaptic protein synapsin I (Fig. 1H,I), indicating a recruitment to synapses.\". Experimental description: Experiment of immunohistochemistry are made in rat.\nLiteral from M&M\n\"Rat dissociated hippocampal or cortical neurons from postnatal day 1 pups of either sex were plated at a density of 45,000 cells/cm2 onto poly-d-lysine-coated coverslips, glass-bottomed 35 mm dishes (hippocampal cultures)\n\n15/5/2017 Pim\nExperiments use a HA-tagged overexpression construct. The species of this was construct was **mouse**. Literal: \"Mouse HA-tagged Nedd4-1 in pCDNA3.1(-) was purchased from the Addgene DNA repository.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_538" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

